		(property "Description" "DPDT slide switch, RS-485 termination. Common pins (2, 5) are the switch wiper; pole 1 (pins 1-3) routes the 120R termination resistor in/out of the A/B pair, pole 2 (pins 4-6) ganged on the same physical actuator reports termination state to GPIO10 (pin 4 = GND so the position that inserts the 120R also reads LOW = terminated). See docs/MODULAR_PANEL_COUNT.md."
